@NODE Usage "ANSI renderer v0.2 - Usage"

@{b}ANSI RENDERER@{ub}'s interface has been  designed as a very simple affair, and is
quite  straight  forward.   Still,  for all the uninitiated, we are about to
take  a  trip  through  ANSI land, and demonstrate a typical session of ANSI
generation.


@{b}@{u}Load IFF (shortcut keystroke is L)@{ub}@{uu}

Loads  a  @{i}75  by  28@{ui}  pixel  big  IFF brush/picture, in any resolution.  The
brush/picture cannot contain more than @{i}8 colours@{ui} (3 bitplanes).


@{b}@{u}Render (shortcut keystroke is R)@{ub}@{uu}

Evaluates   the  last  loaded  IFF  brush/picture,  and  generates  an  ANSI
evaluation  in  FULL  colour!   On an unexpanded A1200, a FULL SCREEN render
takes  less  than  3 seconds to calculate, so there is NO need to leave your
machine, rendering overnight!!


@{b}@{u}Save Render (shortcut keystroke is S)@{ub}@{uu}

Saves  the last render in ANSI text format.  The saved  file can be directly
displayed  in  the  CLI  window  using the TYPE command, or imported into an
ANSI editor (like @{i}DIED@{ui}) for further editing.


@{b}@{u}Help (shortcut keystrokes are A and the HELP key)@{ub}@{uu}

Displays  this  @{i}AMIGA  GUIDE@{ui} information document. @{i}MULTIVIEW@{ui} must reside in
your default UTILITIES directory.


@{b}@{u}Paint Program (shortcut keystroke is P)@{ub}@{uu}

Selects  the  default paint package (like Cloanto's @{i}Personal Paint@{ui}), through
the  standard ASL requester, to  be used by @{b}ANSI RENDERER@{ub}, when a loaded IFF
brush/picture  needs  to be edited.  Full volume/path and program names must
be  inputted.   Alternatively, volume/path and program names can be directly
typed/edited  in  the  string  gadget,  or selected via the magnifying glass
gadget.


@{b}@{u}Edit IFF brush/picture (shortcut keystroke is the DEL key)@{ub}@{uu}

Lets  you  edit  the  last  loaded IFF brush/picture, via the selected paint
program.


@{b}@{u}Render mode (shortcut keystroke is M)@{ub}@{uu}

@{i}BLOCKY@{ui} produces standard looking ANSI renditions, using "BOX" characters.

@{i}CrAzY cHaRs@{ui} produces ANSI renditions, using randomly generated characters.


