@NODE History "ANSI renderer v0.2 - History time!"

@{b}v0.01@{ub}  (10.12.94)  -  First  version  of  @{b}ANSI RENDERER.  ANSI  RENDERER@{ub} was
coded,  for  the  simple  reason  that I needed a quick and efficient way of
generating  good  looking  ANSI screens for @{b}rOM@{ub}  advertising purposes.  This
version only supported 1 colour ANSI renders.

@{b}v0.10@{ub} (20.02.95) - Added Amiga Guide help support  and direct  paint program
links, via simple gadget clicks.  @{b}ANSI RENDERER@{ub} now  supports up to 4 colour
ANSI  text  generation.  Replaced REQTOOLS requesters with the standard WB2
ASL ones. This is the first releasable version of this tool.

@{b}v0.20@{ub} (30.02.95)  - Added 8 colour  ANSI support.  @{b}ANSI RENDERER@{ub} has now two
render modes; @{i}Blocky@{ui} and @{i}CrAzY cHaRs@{ui}.





